Section 1:
1 L.D. 1428
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 937, L.D. 1428, “An Act to Increase
10 Access to Child Care for Maine Families”
11 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 1 and inserting the following:
12 'Sec. 1. 22 MRSA §8302-A, sub-§4 is enacted to read:
13 4. Recreational space. A child care facility or a family child care provider may
14 operate without an outdoor recreational space as long as an outside public recreational
15 space is available within a reasonable distance from the facility or provider.'
16 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 3.
17 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
18 number to read consecutively.
19 SUMMARY
2200 This amendment allows a child care facility or family child care provider to operate
2211 without an outdoor recreational space as long as an outdoor public recreational space is
2222 available within a reasonable distance rather than being located within one-quarter of a
2233 mile as in the bill. The amendment also removes from the bill the requirement for the
2244 Maine State Housing Authority to amend its rules to allow child care facilities to be located
2255 within projects built using low-income housing tax credits.
2266 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
2277 (See attached)
Page 1 - 132LR1471(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
